  "issue_title": "[BUG] decode_packed_contract_storage accepts short buffers and raises struct.error",
  "issue_body": "## Description\n\n`decode_packed_contract_storage()` validates `len(data) < 74`, but later unpacks `alpha_pool` using `<QQ` at offset 74 (requires 16 additional bytes).  \nAs a result, payloads with length `74..89` pass the guard and then crash with `struct.error`.\n\n## Steps to Reproduce\n1. Open a Python shell in the repo.\n2. Run:\n   ```python\n   from gittensor.validator.issue_competitions.storage_utils import decode_packed_contract_storage\n   decode_packed_contract_storage(bytes(80))\n3. Observe exception raised from struct.unpack_from.\n\n## Expected Behavior\n\nFunction should fail gracefully for short/invalid payloads (e.g., return None), without throwing struct.error.\n\n\n## Actual Behavior\n\nFunction raises struct.error for buffer lengths 74..89.\n\n\n## Additional Context\n\nAffected function:\n\ngittensor/validator/issue_competitions/storage_utils.py\ndecode_packed_contract_storage()\nLikely fix:\n\nRequire at least 90 bytes before unpacking, or compute required size from the struct layout.\nAdd boundary tests for lengths <74, 74..89, and >=90.\n",
  "merged_at": "2026-04-20T21:49:04.000Z",
